metadata.name: Dead Ringers: Edition
metadata.description:
Dead Ringers: Edition

Every day in January 2022 I generated a new output from an algorithm, generated a random wallet address, and sent the work to that address. On the final day, January 31st, all the previous Dead Ringers were placed in a 5 by 6 grid and minted to a generated address.

It was almost guaranteed none of the wallets that received Dead Ringers would ever be accessible given there are 16 to power of 40 available addresses. I hoped it would help observers appreciate the vastness of the address space and the underlying security it provides to the network used to distribute the work.

While the distribution of individual Dead Ringers was extremely fair, as it protected against bots and ballot stuffing, it was also extremely unlikely that they would ever be collected. For that reason, observers ascribed value to their scarcity and the odds of receiving one.

The Dead Ringers: Edition flips that notion on its head. Now an edition of January 31, 2022, colloquially known as the Dead Ringers grid, is available to all wallets as a 24-hour timed edition, capped at the size of 16 to the power of 40. That is the total number of possible wallets, and each wallet is entitled to own one if they should wish.

The ERC1155 token points to the same PNG file on Arweave that the original January 31, 2022 referenced, meaning the underlying artwork is exactly the same file as the sought after original.

Each wallet is only eligible to mint one edition, and if a wallet already has one it cannot mint another. There is a 24 hour minting period and the edition size is capped at 16 to the power of 40, the number of all possible Ethereum addresses.

30 Dead Ringers in a 5 by 6 grid

{"name":"Midnight Calm","description":"The waters were incredibly still, only interrupted by quiet splashing. The hero was rowing the boat in pitch darkness. Feeling exhausted she paused, unsure of her destination. Her instinct brought her here, but she wondered if she had made a mistake. She was about to turn back when the night sky grew brighter, suddenly illuminated by dancing lights. She was instantly mesmerized by the gorgeous sight, breath-taken by the vivid colors that even made the clouds glow.

She noticed a rift in the sky, the thick darkness that slashed through the lights. There the cosmic energy was leaking through. She felt her magic returning and it was washing away any lingering darkness off her magical cloak. Feeling immensely grateful, she was more appreciative of simple things, realizing their transience.

She heard a sound calling out to her- the voice seemed to be all around her. Then she noticed shadows approaching beneath the water's surface, a gigantic creature and her young. She stayed calm and concentrated on what they were trying to tell her.

description:
The waters were incredibly still, only interrupted by quiet splashing. The hero was rowing the boat in pitch darkness. Feeling exhausted she paused, unsure of her destination. Her instinct brought her here, but she wondered if she had made a mistake. She was about to turn back when the night sky grew brighter, suddenly illuminated by dancing lights. She was instantly mesmerized by the gorgeous sight, breath-taken by the vivid colors that even made the clouds glow.

She noticed a rift in the sky, the thick darkness that slashed through the lights. There the cosmic energy was leaking through. She felt her magic returning and it was washing away any lingering darkness off her magical cloak. Feeling immensely grateful, she was more appreciative of simple things, realizing their transience.

She heard a sound calling out to her- the voice seemed to be all around her. Then she noticed shadows approaching beneath the water's surface, a gigantic creature and her young. She stayed calm and concentrated on what they were trying to tell her.

metadata.name: AIXXA #70
metadata.description: It is a form of plant that exists on a planet with constantly changing gravitational flows. They exist in united colonies, floating endlessly in the air taking bizarre shapes and constantly changing color under the influence of temperature, different gases, and radiation of the stars surrounding the planet. Each colony goes through many cycles, migrating along the entire surface of the planet. In places where gravity weakens, plants put down "roots" and attach themselves to the planet's surface. There is still debate about the intelligence (collective intelligence) of AIXXA plants. They are listed as an inheritance of the Vtolmr planetary system and are protected by an intergalactic convention. Only 600 images of these plants were allowed, after which access to the planet was denied to all but the inhabitants of this planetary system. These images depict various forms, phases, and states of AIXXA plant colonies. Unfortunately, some of them are so rare that only a few specimens could be captured. It is believed that anyone who has such an image in their collection can draw endless inspiration from it because these plants are ascribed magical properties. But there is no scientific proof of it. Nevertheless, the hunt for these images by collectors has become legendary and has been described in many works of literature after the 34th century when they were released. This is the TBOA club's first on-chain project.

metadata: {"image":"https://cdn.gen.art/203566_1632149464.png","name":"Caesium Standard #3566","description":"Caesium Standard is a multilayered interactive generative art project that blurs geometry, abstraction & generative art. It explores interactive methods through the artistic production of the conceptual moving image. Our artwork is a kind of thought experiment that emerges for the audience, raising questions about the blockchain, time, and aesthetic implications of artificial visual worlds. It offers the collector the experience of trapping time on time blockchain and GEN.ART hash codes and interpreting all these concepts together. \\\n\\\nBy **I'M NOT MINIMAL (Okan Uckun & Orkhan Mammadov)** \\\nLicense: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0","external_url":"https://gen.art/gallery/2/203566","animation_url":"https://api.gen.art/public/live/203566","attributeCount":11}
name: Caesium Standard #3566
description:
Caesium Standard is a multilayered interactive generative art project that blurs geometry, abstraction & generative art. It explores interactive methods through the artistic production of the conceptual moving image. Our artwork is a kind of thought experiment that emerges for the audience, raising questions about the blockchain, time, and aesthetic implications of artificial visual worlds. It offers the collector the experience of trapping time on time blockchain and GEN.ART hash codes and interpreting all these concepts together. \
\
By **I'M NOT MINIMAL (Okan Uckun & Orkhan Mammadov)** \

{"title":"Uniqueness is in the soul of the beholder","name":"Uniqueness is in the soul of the beholder","type":"object","imageUrl":"https://ipfsgateway.makersplace.com/ipfs/QmWx4dLi6rRd6v1e6jpXoZyQ57C9ZVUEGaAs7YoRjCxhV5","description":"What is the soul? What will save our soul? Who will save our soul? A question only time may tell, if ever. Unlikely the other pieces in this series, this one is a little more put together, a little smoother, and maybe a little more important. It's all just a simulation anyway, right?

Projections of the geometric form in the center are mapped to spheres orbiting the central figure. Although technically they are all observing the same geometric form, their perspective is warped due to their vantage point and position. Ultimately, uniqueness is in fact in the soul of the beholder.

The video is perfectly looped and despite containing elements of noise to appear random it starts and ends in the same state. The elements of perceived freedom and randomness are in fact an illusion, despite what you may be led to feel.

As a generative artist I write code that outputs unique versions of my work although the code remains the same. Uniqueness is at core of generative art, and uniqueness is at the core of cryptography.

This piece is part of a series, see also "Uniqueness is in the heart of the beholder", and "Uniqueness is in the eye of the beholder", and "Uniqueness is in the mind of the beholder".

name: Uniqueness is in the soul of the beholder
description:
What is the soul? What will save our soul? Who will save our soul? A question only time may tell, if ever. Unlikely the other pieces in this series, this one is a little more put together, a little smoother, and maybe a little more important. It's all just a simulation anyway, right?

Projections of the geometric form in the center are mapped to spheres orbiting the central figure. Although technically they are all observing the same geometric form, their perspective is warped due to their vantage point and position. Ultimately, uniqueness is in fact in the soul of the beholder.

The video is perfectly looped and despite containing elements of noise to appear random it starts and ends in the same state. The elements of perceived freedom and randomness are in fact an illusion, despite what you may be led to feel.

As a generative artist I write code that outputs unique versions of my work although the code remains the same. Uniqueness is at core of generative art, and uniqueness is at the core of cryptography.

This piece is part of a series, see also "Uniqueness is in the heart of the beholder", and "Uniqueness is in the eye of the beholder", and "Uniqueness is in the mind of the beholder".

2048px by 2048px, 480 frames, ~20 seconds, loop

The video is perfectly looped and despite containing elements of noise to appear random it starts and ends in the same state. The elements of perceived freedom and randomness are in fact an illusion, despite what you may be led to feel.

As a generative artist I write code that outputs unique versions of my work although the code remains the same. Uniqueness is at core of generative art, and uniqueness is at the core of cryptography.

This piece is part of a series, see also "Uniqueness is in the heart of the beholder", and "Uniqueness is in the eye of the beholder", and "Uniqueness is in the mind of the beholder".

2048px by 2048px, 480 frames, ~20 seconds, loop

metadata.name: Curse NFT. Standard Ticket.
metadata.description:
A backstage photo of model Krystall Schott was taken during New York Fashion Week 2016 and became the uncredited #1 search for "face" on Google. After years of being unable to counter her algorithmic curse, smart contract technology has made it possible for Krystall to reclaim her authority over her face and narrative once more.

The Standard Ticket is a looping film of Krystall Schott behind the scenes at PROTAGON during the making of Curse NFT, with music by Barrett Avner.

The Standard Ticket is a limited edition collectible ERC721 NFT, with 700/1000 mints.

Holding this ticket will ensure access to the private auction of Curse NFT and the Accursed Share Discord channel.

If all 1000 tickets are sold, Accursed Share will allocate funds to create a streamlined and accessible web application that allows artists to mint their own dynamic NFTs using Chainlink's Keeper technology. The initial platform will enable artists to create NFTs similar in function to Curse NFT. This will be an open sourced project and a first gift from Accursed Share to the NFT community, to help bridge the gap between artists and developers, and jumpstart an era of accessible NFT innovation.

Ticket holders will be able to burn their tickets in exchange for early access to this platform.

Credits: Model: Krystall Schott / Producers: Accursed Share (Monica Belevan, John Thomas Connor, Charles Curran); PROTAGON (Brian Adler); Krystall Schott / Executive Producer: Brian Adler / Visual Effects and 3D Scanning: PROTAGON / Photography: Pat Bombard / Hair: Tyeler Perfect / Make-up: Christina Lee Adams / Music: Barrett Avner / Engineers: The DeFi Network

Curse NFT is an Accursed Share production, in association with PROTAGON.

{"description":"DEAFBEEF: Generative On-Chain Multimedia Art The code and parameters to generate and reconstruct these multimedia files is stored on the Ethereum blockchain. Series 0 - Synth Poems - Token 2 Synth Poems are 1min generative audiovisual pieces using FM synthesis, and XY oscilloscope visualization. Each entirely generated unsupervised by a self contained code model, which is stored on chain.

Frequency Modulation(FM) is a method that was used in broadcasting radio signals, later discovered to be useful for audio synthesis allowing a simply way to generate rich harmonic timbres. The left and right stereo audio channels are mapped to the XY inputs of a (virtual) oscilloscope to produce a direct visualization of the audio waveform.

At the musical level, this generative algorithm plays with feedback to produce an evolving but balanced set of timbres and pitches. Across pieces, a carefully selected set of rules govern the variation of tempos, time signatures, (in)harmonicity resulting in individual pieces that are unique, while retaining a common theme. DEAFBEEF: Generative On-Chain Multimedia Art The code and parameters to generate and reconstruct these multimedia files is stored on the Ethereum blockchain. Series 0 - Synth Poems - Token 2 Synth Poems are 1min generative audiovisual pieces using FM synthesis, and XY oscilloscope visualization. Each entirely generated unsupervised by a self contained code model, which is stored on chain.

Frequency Modulation(FM) is a method that was used in broadcasting radio signals, later discovered to be useful for audio synthesis allowing a simply way to generate rich harmonic timbres. The left and right stereo audio channels are mapped to the XY inputs of a (virtual) oscilloscope to produce a direct visualization of the audio waveform.

At the musical level, this generative algorithm plays with feedback to produce an evolving but balanced set of timbres and pitches. Across pieces, a carefully selected set of rules govern the variation of tempos, time signatures, (in)harmonicity resulting in individual pieces that are unique, while retaining a common theme.

Digital Objects is on hiatus.

This was an experiment in supporting digital artists by making their artworks collectible via ERC-721 tokens. Our goal was to help artists sell their work directly to a new class of collectors.

While a small community has formed around this new kind of collecting, we learned that it will likely take years to gain enough adoption to support a company.

We're sad to put things on hold — we still believe in the concept, and hope to get involved again in the future.

For collector or artist support, please email us.

Thank you,
The Digital Objects team

metadata.name: The Night Watch RE-immortalized on the Blockchain
metadata.description: The famous painting by Rembrandt van Rijn currently hangs in Amsterdam at the Rijksmuseum.  Painting is said to immortalize its subject, however this is a physical item, and the oil paint cracks and deteriorates after time.  As time passes, nothing is certain, war and famine, loss of funds by the museum, vandalism, theft or the unknown could take this artwork from us. This painting image, which was created by an Artist and his team almost four decades ago, and the artist work is currently in the public domain, which is meant to be owned by the public.  However, the work has never been sold since Rembrandt was paid 1,600 guilders for his painting, which at today's exchange would be about 726 euros, or 828 US dollars.  Since it was commissioned by the a municipal institution the actual painting belongs to the city of Amsterdam, is considered priceless, will never be sold, and the museum charges a entry fee to view the piece.  Looking at the piece on google requires you to view adds, and sacrifice your privacy to cookies and trackers, which comes at a cost too.  This digital copy however can hang in the truly open domain on the Blockchain, be viewed freely by everyone with an internet connection, and can be owned by everyone, including you.

Looking at the piece on google requires you to view adds, and sacrifice your privacy to cookies and trackers, which comes at a cost too.  This digital copy however can hang in the truly open domain on the Blockchain, be viewed freely by everyone with an internet connection, and can be owned by everyone, including you.
